data.description: Beautiful Acadian Historical home with open floor plan and all the charm and character you would expect of a home that was once part of Cinclaire Plantation. Located on a quiet cul de sac with great neighbors, this 3/4 bedroom, 2 full baths with custom tile work will give you plenty of room to entertain friends and family. This home has been completely renovated with new windows, plantation shutters throughout, new roof, new HVAC, new pex plumbing and updated electrical. Custom pine flooring throughout, granite kitchen countertops with all new stainless steel appliances and a 5-Burner gas range.  There is a large pantry and laundry room with a barn door, which is located conveniently next to the kitchen and breakfast area.  This home also features a large formal dining room as well. There are two living rooms to be utilized as a bonus/flex space, fourth bedroom or office.  This home also contains ample cabinet space and closets in all rooms. You have to see the size of the bedrooms and ceiling height to appreciate the possibilities of this home.  New lighting fixtures and ceiling fans throughout. The front and back porches allow for outdoor entertaining under the large oak tree. This home is nestled between BHS, BMS and the Upper Elementary School.  This home's  location is truly in the heart of Brusly, near the levee and new park. Look no further, this is the home for you!  Just minutes from the bridge, shopping, restaurants and all school activities.  Call today for your personal tour, before this home goes under contract!
